The United States welcomes the Republic of Korea's adoption of its new Indo-Pacific Strategy, which reflects a shared commitment to the region's security and prosperity. The strategy emphasizes universal values such as the rule of law and human rights and aims to expand cooperation with allies and partners in the Indo-Pacific. This will strengthen international peace, security, and nuclear nonproliferation efforts. Additionally, the strategy will enhance economic security networks, cooperation in science and technology, and engagement on climate change and energy security. The United States applauds President Yoon and the ROK's leadership and congratulates the people of the ROK on their new strategy, which will contribute to a free, peaceful, and prosperous Indo-Pacific.